@node SETSTROKECAP

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETSTROKECAP                                                                @{FG Text}@{UU}

Purpose: Sets the stroke cap for an object, or for a stroke style tag. If
         nothing is selected, it sets the stroke cap for future objects.

Syntax:  @{b}setstrokecap@{ub} <BUTT | ROUND | SQUARE> [ALL | STROKENUMBER number/I]
         [DOCUMENT name/S | WINDOW name/S | OBJECTID number/I |
         STYLETAG name/S]

Format:  @{U}Parameter@{UU}    @{U}Values to enter@{UU}
         BUTT         sets a butt cap.
         ROUND        sets a round cap.
         SQUARE       sets a square cap.
         ALL          sets the cap for all strokes. (Default)
         STROKENUMBER sets the cap of a specific stroke number. (See note)
         DOCUMENT     is the document name.
         WINDOW       is the window name.
         OBJECTID     is the number of the object. (Default=current)
         STYLETAG     **

Notes:   STROKENUMBER: Strokes are numbered from 0. This is different than
         the program interface which numbers them from 1.

Example: setstrokecap butt
         setstrokecap round strokenumber 1 object

@{" Command Format    " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/FORM}
@{" Object ID numbers " link PageStream3:Help/PGS.MSU/IDNU}
